oai_dc:dc.dc:title: COMPOSITE BREAKWATER AT TAICHUNG HARBOR, R.O.C.
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Wu, Chung-Chuang
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Taichung Harbor
breakwater
composite breakwater
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The composite type breakwater used in Taichung Harbor contributes economical cross section and better consideration of drifting sand control. Also, with the plan of making caissons on the sand beach and installing caissons by using an unprecedented "Island" method, it shorten the construction period of breakwater significantly.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 20 (1986): Proceedings of 20th Conference on Coastal Engineering, Taipei, Taiwan, 1986.; 175
